summaries.short: Kari opens up to Siri, while Bilzi struggles to hide a shameful truth. Elena finds new ways to earn her keep. Sheriff Willman struggles to hide his shame from Ingrid. The bootleggers face a dilemma.
summaries.full: As Kari opens up about her past, Bilzi struggles to hide a shameful truth. After a run-in with Elena, Siri vows to keep Marin from Finn and deals with the consequences of her own fateful choice. As customs agents close in, the bootleggers find themselves in a bind.

summaries.short: The men of Utmark go on a wolf hunt. Meanwhile, Marin does her best to defend her mother, Siri grows closer to Kari, and Finn finds himself with yet another questionable houseguest.
summaries.full: The men of Utmark finally decide to do something about their wolf problem – with shocking consequences. Meanwhile, left without a responsible adult to turn to, a desperate Marin threatens Heige’s secret. As her relationship with Bilzi deteriorates, Siri grows closer to Kari, while Finn is forced to take in yet another unwanted houseguest.

summaries.short: Just as Finn nears rock bottom, Stein forces him to take in an unwelcome guest. Bilzi takes control of his newfound family, while Willman attempts to hide his mounting debt from Ingrid.
summaries.full: As Finn reaches rock bottom, Siri does her best to help Marin reconcile with her dad, while Bilzi posits himself as a new father figure. Stein foists a scarred Elena onto Finn as he struggles to find customers, Håvard deals with his ex, and Sheriff Willman slips further into debt.

summaries.short: As Bilzi reconnects with a figure from his past, Finn confides in Marin, and Siri grows closer to Kari. While Stein works through his grief, Willman experiences a win.
summaries.full: As a mysterious figure returns from Bilzi’s past, Finn finally confides in Marin, and Siri explores complex feelings with Kari. Later, Willman sees the light, while Stein works through his grief with a little help from Drita.

summaries.short: As the feud between Bilzi and Finn boils over, Marin turns to Kari for help. Meanwhile, Stein faces a snag in his scheme, Håvard shares shocking news with Helene, and Sheriff Willman deals with mounting debts.
summaries.full: As Bilzi continues his reign of terror on Finn’s flock, Marin struggles to find an adult capable of shouldering her many problems. After Sheriff Willman proves unhelpful, Finn’s descent into depression lands him in serious trouble with Stein. Meanwhile, Håvard’s ex Helene comes to terms with a shocking revelation.

titles.short: And They Lived Happily Ever After
titles.full: And They Lived Happily Ever After

summaries.short: Tensions reach an all-time high as the annual church bazaar looms on the horizon, bringing spiritual issues – and secrets – to the surface.
summaries.full: As the citizens of Utmark prepare to gather for the annual bazaar, Dagrun turns to the church for help with a spiritual issue, Willman battles his own demons, and Marja prepares for what lies beyond. Later, Drita and Elena tackle an unexpected boon, Marin gives Siri an ultimatum, and Finn risks another battle with Bilzi when he turns to an unexpected ally for a business proposition.

summaries.short: As bootleggers arrive in Utmark, Bilzi mourns a loss, Marin uncovers a dark secret, and Finn continues his downward spiral. Meanwhile, Stein makes a questionable investment.
summaries.full: After a devastating death, Bilzi’s mourning throws Siri for a loop, while Marin uncovers her father’s dark secret. Grieving his own loss, Stein attempts to fill the void with an illegal acquisition. Later, Finn’s downward spiral continues with the arrival of a pair of foreign bootleggers.
